Galtin, I wholeheartedly agree with you about your philosophy on grouping.  Pickup groups and Sorcerors don't mix at all.  Find a group of good friends and try level up with them that way you'll learn how to mesh well with eachother and exp will be the most productive.  Unfortunatley I have to disagree with the rest of your post.  Most importantly about pets...<P>Pets are extremely useful for us, without them we are extremely disadvantaged.  Especially since we get the strongest pets in the game... Nobody else gets a level 50 pet.  Not specing mind enough to get the 41-50 charm is a crime!!!  Exping in a group without a pet is fine BUT no pet in rvr will make you half as poweful. lvl 50 pets hit HARD and if you're dueling someone you will lose without a strong pet this i can guarantee.  Mind is in my opinion primary an RvR spec even if mez is nerfed the con/str debuff is still our most important spell.  I've said it so many times, the highest con/str debuff will cut down a midgard tanks hps by 50%+ hps and on any anything else 75%+.  It is our most powerful spell....Of course specing 44 into mind is alot and perhaps not needed depended on your style of play, but i do know that you want level 50 pets don't even think of not specing mind to 33........
