<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Zaelthus:<BR><STRONG> Not specing mind enough to get the 41-50 charm is a crime!!!  Exping in a group without a pet is fine BUT no pet in rvr will make you half as poweful. lvl 50 pets hit HARD and if you're dueling someone you will lose without a strong pet this i can guarantee.....but i do know that you want level 50 pets don't even think of not specing mind to 33........</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Well here is my line of reasoning that led me to assume having a level 41+ pet in RvR is not that big of a deal.  Almost every robed caster I have talked to in game states they don't live that long in RvR.  Most of the posts from robed casters on the IGN Dev board state the same thing.  So even if I have a level 41+ pet, I'll lose it when I die.  I'm an optimist at heart, but in this game I always go into RvR assuming I will die fairly early in the fight.  At that point, I'll either get a rez (if we win) or release (if we lose).  Even if I get a rez, most likely I won't be in a position to go get another pet, especially if I'm seiging or defending a keep, which so far seems to be the main focus of RvR.  So the assumption is that most of the time that I will be RvRing, I won't have access to a pet even if I specced Mind to 32.  If that is a true assumption, then those points could be better spent elsewhere.    <P>So its a classic tradeoff.  Which is better for RvR?  If I spec Mind up to 33, I would have a level 41+ pet and a 107 pt STR/CON debuff.  If I stop speccing Mind at 25, my max pet is level 40 (which should still be an asset in RvR) and my STR/CON debuff is 82 pts.  But I also get whatever new spells are in the Matter spec list plus better nukes and an AE root from the Body spec list.  I am assuming the versatility this course of action provides would be better for RvR compared to focusing on speccing Mind up to 33.<P>Of course this is all speculation on my part assuming the new Matter spells are worth spending points on. <P>Galtin
